Champion Select[]

Original
Marauder
Each of these skins may feature: a voiceover filter; additional quotes and/or interactions. In all other cases, skins use the base skin's audio or version of the audio. Some voicelines may also be disabled while using alternate skins.
For Skaarl's pool of voicelines not listed alongside the conversations with Kled, see below, in separate section.

Trivia[]

Kled & Skaarl, the Cantankerous Cavaliers
  • ▶️   "Holy ****, where are we?" has the curse bleeped over for ESRB rating concerns, as well as for other ratings (League of Legends is rated T for 13-year-olds and above by ESRB) as well as humorous purposes.
  • ▶️   "Of course you realize, this means war" references Bugs Bunny from Looney Tunes.
  • ▶️   "I dont need nothing but this axe... and this gun... and this hat" references The Jerk.
  • ▶️   "I'm Kled, and this here's Skaarl. Prepare to die" references Inigo Montoya from The Princess Bride.
  • ▶️   "Don't try and understand 'em, just rope, throw and brand 'em." is a reference to the song Rawhide.
  • ▶️   "Serenity now!" references an episode from Seinfeld.
  • ▶️   "It's go time!" might be referencing Seinfeld as well.
  • ▶️   "This! Is! Noxus!" references the movie 300.
  • ▶️   "Nice axe! Learn to use it!" is similar to Draven's quote "Nice axe—I'll take it!".
  • ▶️   "Yeah, yeah, invade Ionia you said, it'll be fine you said!" references the meme It Will Be Fun, They Said.
  • ▶️   "Y'know, a long time ago, being crazy meant something." is a quote by Charles Manson.
  • ▶️   "Too stupid to live, too dumb to die." references Raoul Duke from Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas.
  • ▶️   "I hate to advocate violence and insanity, but it's worked for me." is a play on a quote by author Hunter S. Thompson.
  • ▶️   "Noxus was created to train the faithful." references Dune.
  • Kled shares quotes with:
    • ▶️   ▶️   "Die!"
